description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and dynamic Staff Nurse to join our busy Ophthalmic Outpatient team. We are a busy department that provides a range of services for patients of all ages with ophthalmic conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate&#39;s duties will consist of co-ordinating a range of ophthalmic specialist clinics, whilst providing a high standard of patient care. You will also have the opportunity to assist with minor ophthalmic operations, participate in our nurse led clinics and facilitate the delivery of IVT for the retinal service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to learn new skills with no experience is necessary as competencies and training are provided in-house.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills are essential for this post as much of the nursing care we provide relates to health promotion. You will need to be able to work effectively as part of the team and efficiently when required to work autonomously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLISA WARNERJob titleMATRONEmail addresslisawarner@nhs.netTelephone number0300 1314500 ext 3016Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or an informal discussion please contact Matron Lisa Warner on 03001314500 ext. 3016.&lt;/p&gt;
